pv3199.lib.java.util

Class Classes

  • java.lang.Object
    • pv3199.lib.java.util.Classes

  • public final class Classes
extends Object
    Utilities for Class objects, such as determining whether or not a primitive type can be casted to a certain object type, or the class of the deepest component in an array.
    Author:
    Vishal Patel

      • primitiveCastTypes

        private static Class<?>[] primitiveCastTypes(Class<?> prim)
        An array of unknown generic type primitive classes representing what one primitive data type can be casted to. boolean always returns boolean.class while any other primitive data type returns all other primitive classes.
        Parameters:
        prim - - the primitive class.
        Returns:
        null if the primitive class is null or is not actually a primitive class; boolean.class if prim == boolean.class in an array of unknown generic typed classes; otherwise an array of of unknown generic typed classes filled with every primitive class except for boolean.class

      • canCastPrimitiveToPrimitive

        public static boolean canCastPrimitiveToPrimitive(Class<?> prim1,
                                                  Class<?> prim2)
        Checks whether one primitive type can be casted into another primitive type.
        Parameters:
        prim1 - - the first primitive type to cast.
        prim2 - - the second primitive type to be casted to.
        Returns:
        true if the cast is possible; false if either of the parameters are null or if the cast is not possible.

      • canCastObjectToObject

        public static boolean canCastObjectToObject(Class<?> obj1,
                                            Class<?> obj2)
        Checks whether an object type can be casted into another object type. Wrapper classes are included (Boolean can only be casted into itself, while Character, Byte, Short, Integer, Long, Float, and Double can all cast into one another).
        Parameters:
        obj1 - - the object type to cast.
        obj2 - - the object type to cast to.
        Returns:
        true if the first object type can cast into the second object type; false otherwise.

      • canCast

        public static boolean canCast(Class<?> clazz1,
                              Class<?> clazz2)
        Checks if one class can be casted to another class. Includes cross-primitive-wrapper casts such as a primitive int to a wrapper Double.
        Parameters:
        clazz1 - - the original class.
        clazz2 - - the desired casted class.
        Returns:
        true if the original class can be casted to the desired class.

      • primitiveToPrimitiveCast

        public static Object primitiveToPrimitiveCast(Object primitive,
                                              Class<?> newPrimitiveType)
        Casts a primitive data into another primitive data.
        Parameters:
        primitive - - the primitive data to cast.
        newPrimitiveType - - the primitive data type to cast to.
        Returns:
        null if either of the parameters are null, if the primitive data given was not wrapped, or if the primitive data cannot be casted into the new specified primitive data type; an Object wrapping casted primitive data otherwise.
        Throws:
        IllegalArgumentException - if the primitive argument does not have a wrapper equivalent class

      • strictComponentCheck

        public static boolean strictComponentCheck(Class<?> array,
                                           Class<?> clazz)
        Strictly checks if an array has some element in any of its dimensions whose class is the EXACT same as another class. Unlike componentCheck(Class, Class), wrapper classes are not checked for data equality against primitive classes and utilizes the == comparison operator.
        Parameters:
        array - - the array to check upon.
        clazz - - the given class to check the array's element with.
        Returns:
        true if the array has some element in any of its dimensions whose class is the EXACT same as the given class.

      • componentCheck

        public static boolean componentCheck(Class<?> array,
                                     Class<?> clazz)
        Checks if an array has some element in any of its dimensions whose class is equivalent as another class. If the element's class is primitive, then the element's wrapper class equivalent is used for equality checking. For example, given Double[][].class and double.class, the method returns true.
        Parameters:
        array - - the array to check upon.
        clazz - - the given class to check the array's element with.
        Returns:
        true if the array has some element in any of its dimensions whose class is equivalent to the given class.
